CatDescriptText: Cutline of related similar image by another photographer of same event published in Pittsburgh Post Gazette November 9, 1944, reads: "Mozelle Thompson, who lives at 5132 Schenley Avenue yesterday received two prizes, amounting to $210, for his pictures which won recognition in the contest conducted by the Women's National Institute for the United States Time Corporation. Edith Belfour Dunn, left, representing the institute, and Jean Thoburn, center, Peabody art teacher, here congratulate Mozelle after the prizes were awarded at a special assembly at Peabody. - Post-Gazette Photo."
TitMainTitle: Woman, possibly Mrs. Thompson, and Mozelle Thompson looking at prize given to him for his artwork, possibly in Peabody High School
